			<div class="content" id="post-content-2489700">
									

<p><strong>TLDR</strong>: <a href="http://www.scpper.com">www.scpper.com</a> - statistics and information here. Good stuff.</p>
<p>Hello, everyone. You may or may not remember me as the guy who made an <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1076362/scpper-a-chrome-extension-for-browsing-scp">extension for Chrome</a> to make browsing SCP wikis a little more enjoyable.<br />
At some point during the development of this extension, SCPper, I decided that I need to have a database, to pull various information from. Said and done. But then I felt like potential of this database would be wasted if it was only a crutch for for SCPper.<br />
Long story short, I made <a href="http://www.scpper.com">ScpperDB</a> - a site which provides web interface to said database, allowing people to find various statistics about individual pages, users or wikis as a whole. For example, you can find how page's rating changed over time, see all pages user voted on, find out what's your ranking among all authors on site, see a list of translations for a page, etc.<br />
If you have any questions, check out my <a href="http://scpper.com/about">mini-FAQ</a>.</p>
<p>I have to admit, this project is my first experience in the field of web-development, since I'm more of back-end kind of guy, so design (and compatibility) can be pretty meh, particularly on smaller screens. A also do not know how my hosting will manage the realistic load. Time will tell, I suppose.</p>
<h5><span>That being said, if you have any question not covered by FAQ, if you find any bugs, errors or if you have any suggestions or ideas how I can improve this site, please, do not hesitate to post in this thread or send a PM over Wikidot.</span></h5>
<p>I hope this site will become a useful tool for you skippers out there.<br />
Cheers.</p>

